Text.Value: It sounds valuable. On second thought, I'll take it all.
*Vague notions of rumour and myth - nothing solid comes to mind.*
Tell Laridda I'm dead. It's the best way.
Don't be stupid. We're parting ways here. Up to you in how many pieces.
What's to say? You're Nere's bootlicker - saw you sail in. A godsdamned True Soul.
I'll need to know a little more about your so-called 'mission' before I let you go.
Damn right, pecker. Now shut your face before I melt it clean off.
The mission comes first. A vial's what I can spare you.
Are you sure about this? Once you're dead, that's it. It's over.
Runepowder, you mean. Such a damned waste...
The powder's 'the reason you're here'? How so?
And I thought I'd heard it all. That's some cambion-level deception.
Your head. It will make a nice souvenir.
I go where there's shit to stir. And there's no shortage of options.
Wait. What in the hells?
Hold on. There's something different about that powder.
Spit out what you want and let's be done with it.
Call me a hoon again.
Take the vial.
Smile sincerely and hold out your hand.
I'm getting the runepowder back to Baldur's Gate. Alone.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'The' ponounced with a long E. THE END.

Text.Value: I knew I couldn't trust you. Do it, then. Make it hurt.
So you'll just leave your clan behind?
What I want is your help. Beldron's trapped - I need the smokepowder.
You want to barter with runepowder -

EditorData.NodeContext: Aghast, catches herself.

Text.Value: Let me go, and you'll be on the right side of history - that's all I can say.
You will not serve Ironhand in death. But you might still serve him in life.
You want to waste runepowder on -

EditorData.NodeContext: Aghast, catches herself.

Text.Value: 'Runepowder'? I thought that was a children's story.
Dead? Of course. They should have run, had every chance.
Try me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Defiant, angry

Text.Value: She's heartless. Delicious.
Hold it. I swear to Ironhand, one more step and I blow us to chunks!

EditorData.NodeContext: Ready to blow you and her up.

Text.Value: Drugh. Dropping my name like your cultist arse knows me. Like we're friends.
Words. I'm about more than that.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bitter and angrt

Text.Value: Drugh. F-fine.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly scared, hesitant

Text.Value: She's gonna blow up. That's my thing.
You'd abandon your beloved? That's mighty cruel of you.
Chk - the gnome's well and truly mad.
Philomeen, I presume. What's going on here?
Laridda? Drugning mind games. I know all about your tricks, True Soul.

EditorData.NodeContext: Mocking you, still crazy

Text.Value: But let me go... and maybe I'll spare you a vial.
What use is a single vial?
How about a little of that smokepowder?
I don't want you. I just wanted the smokepowder.
Gaerdal Ironhand, I have lived for you, and now I'll die for you!
Not a True Soul? And I'm - I'm supposed to believe that?

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with some doubt in her voice. She believes you JUST enough.

Text.Value: Then prove it and leave.
Listen...

EditorData.NodeContext: Our business is concluded, but she's mulling over whether to ask us a favour. She's not one to agonise so her own reluctance annoyes her (this leads into 'You see Laridda at the dig?'

Text.Value: She's leaving? Laridda will be heartbroken.
*A formula so dangerous it was stricken from history - if it ever existed to begin with.*
Cast Detect Thoughts.
Hells. Whatever you do, don't set her off.
What good is a single vial?
Where will you go now?
Holy hells. Have you gone mad?
I'm not sure I blame her. Though Laridda might.
Shut your mouth, hoon, or I'll shut you down.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hoon = outsider, an expletive of sorts. Pronounced like it is spelled.
EditorData.logicalname: Said if companion spoke their line

Text.Value: Don't be dumb. Check your exits - you've got nowhere to go.
Look. We're freedom fighters. We need this powder to a prove a point. To people who really need a point proven to them.
I'm not here to hurt you. You have my word.
Calm down. Let's talk this through.
A vial's all I got... wait...
Now you're getting it. I'd sooner walk the Hells than be tortured at Moonrise!

EditorData.NodeContext: Seething with anger.

Text.Value: I'm not stupid, you know. No such thing in Grymforge as kind hearts.
She has a heart made of stone, this one - that only smokepowder can break.
I know what you are - one of Nere's cult-goons. Sailed right in.
It's the whole damn reason we're here, and I'm not leaving without it.

EditorData.stateContext: Philomeen's hand is lowered. She is not panicked.

Text.Value: Ah, 'playing dead'? A classic ploy.
*Runepowder is gnomish folklore - an explosive of awesome power, handed down to the gnomes by their war-god Gaerdal Ironhand.*
Don't talk of my clan like you understand.
I'll spare you a vial.
Just make it work, all right?
I want nothing from you, I swear.
Better to die in this shit-heap than rot in Moonrise. You want me? Come get me.
... it's gone? You damned rat. I knew I couldn't trust you!
Probably. She's the gullible sort.
'Course I am. You got the runepowder. So now you cut and run.
Smokepowder's no toy. Whatever happens to me, it will be far worse for you.
I don't care. Go on, blow us up.
Your friends are dead. And you will be too if you don't flee this place.
Laridda? Ruddy mind games. I... I know all about your tricks, True Soul.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with some doubt in her voice. She has JUST enough fondness for Laridda to be convinced.

Text.Value: Oh, for... I'm gonna blow, and you're getting chummy? Drugh off, prickslit.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seething with anger.

Text.Value: A vial's all I got left. And I'm not parting with it for nothing.
Don't do this. Don't pretend you - you give a shit about me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with some doubt in her voice. She believes you JUST enough.

Text.Value: Well, it's real, and I need to bring it back to Baldur's Gate.
Beloved? I might have been hers. She sure as hells wasn't mine.
I'm getting gone. You ought to do the same.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'The' ponounced with a long E. THE END.

Text.Value: I'll do worse to Nere's lapdog, hoon.
Do it. I could do with a show.
*But the scent is acrid, as if contaminated somehow. Or much, much more concentrated.*
Ah, nothing says 'true love' like faking your own death to avoid someone.

EditorData.stateContext: Philomeen is on edge and holds a fire in her hand, threatening to blow up the explosive barrels with her.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [S_UND_HiddenGnome] Philomeen sighs and lowers her hand. The flame goes out. She need to end with her hand lowered (SimonG)
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Philomeen sighs and lowers her hand. The flame goes out.

Text.Value: Careful. I'd rather not have to pick bits of gnome from my hair.
Calm down. Beldron's trapped in a cave-in, and I needed the smokepowder.
As an expert on the subject, my dear lady - I'd like to point out that blowing oneself up is never the solution.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's addressing the gnome, not the player.

Text.Value: 'Runepowder'? I thought that was a burrow-tale.
I don't want you. I will take that smokepowder, though.
Friends? Cowards, more like. Gave them a good blast as cover, and they sat on their bony arses. Done for good with them.

EditorData.NodeContext: Calling out to her lover who is not actually there.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [S_UND_HiddenGnome] She do a fireball spell casting anticipation
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Laridda prepares to fling her spell. Transition to gameplay: Laridda fires the spell and blows herself up.
EditorData.SFXTags: SFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] She do a fireball spell casting anticipation
EditorData.VFXTags: VFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] She do a fireball spell casting anticipation

Text.Value: Liar.

EditorData.SFXTags: SFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] She relights her flame
EditorData.VFXTags: VFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] She relights her flame

Text.Value: Calm down. Beldron's trapped in a cave-in, and I need the smokepowder.
Your friends are freed and gathering across the lake. You should join them.

EditorData.logicalname: Beldron is freed, gets gnomes to safety

Text.Value: You see Laridda at the dig? Tell her I'm dead. Impaled, half-eaten... I don't care - make up a story.
Well aren't you sweet?

EditorData.NodeContext: Super sarcastic

Text.Value: Go on, drag me to Moonrise. I'll make you cult-nutters suffer.
'Runepowder'? I thought that was a burrow-tale.
Then let it be done.

EditorData.NodeContext: Creepy sounding. She is taking pleasure in her murder-suicide.

Text.Value: Laridda sent me. The gnomes need your help.
Fine - I've heard all I need.
Look. You have no idea what you're dealing with. Any true Ironhand would trade their life for a grain of this stuff.

EditorData.NodeContext: Steadying her voice and continuing - she was reacting with horror to our ignorance

Text.Value: Deal.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: She tosses the player a vial (throw and catch with hands off-screen, preferably)

Text.Value: Gaerdal Ironhand, hear me now - set me free!

EditorData.NodeContext: About to blow herself up, thinking she is dying an honorable death.

Text.Value: If I was a True Soul, you'd be dead. Stand down before you hurt yourself.
Look at me - I'm not here to hurt my own.
'Runepowder'? I thought that was a children's story.
Shit. I can't do it.

EditorData.SFXTags: SFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] Her flame goes out
EditorData.VFXTags: VFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] Her flame goes out

Text.Value: Laridda needs you. So does your crew - your burrow.
What the drugh? You - you know nothing of me, damn it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with some doubt in her voice. She believes you JUST enough.

Text.Value: Very generous of you - I accept.
*An ashen scent fills the air. The barrel is filled with smokepowder.*

EditorData.SFXTags: [S_UND_HiddenGnome] flame swaps from left to right hand
EditorData.VFXTags: [S_UND_HiddenGnome] flame swaps from left to right hand

Text.Value: Well it's real, and I need to bring it back to Baldur's Gate. I'd rather my clan were with me, but...
I'd rather have the pleasure of killing you with my own hands.
Raise your hands in a show of peace.
Damned nutter. You - you think I fear death?

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with some doubt in her voice. She believes you JUST enough.

Text.Value: Bugger it all - you moved them.

EditorData.SFXTags: SFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] Her flame goes out
EditorData.VFXTags: VFX on [S_UND_HiddenGnome] Her flame goes out

Text.Value: Leave.
Attack.
Drugnin' liars. Wouldn't know truth if it slapped you broadside.

EditorData.NodeContext: Seething with anger.

Text.Value: KILL THE FIRE. OR DIE. PAINFULLY.
I'm not taking you anywhere. You're free to go.
It's the whole damn reason we're here.
That's the point, genius.
I'll pass on the word - right after I kill you.
'Ironhand'. 'Runepowder'. Where have you heard these terms before?
I could tell her I ate you. Think she'd believe me?
I know what you're doing. And it ends, here and now.
Try me, you prick.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Philomeen gestures and the flame in her hand briefly sparks even more.

Text.Value: We've heard the same ones, I bet. A fistful of fire that can turn cities to dust.
Easy now, let's not do anything hilarious.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gnome is threatening to blow herself up, but Astarion is pretty sure he'll survive the blast

Text.Value: A barrel of this could light up the Underdark. A vial is plenty - just let me go my way.
You wouldn't dare - you don't have the courage.
No. No, please!

EditorData.VFXTags: [S_UND_HiddenGnome] A flame appear in her left hand and persist for half the Dialogue

Text.Value: Get moving. I'll be doing the same.

EditorData.logicalname: Told her the others are freed

Text.Value: No deal.

Synopsis:
Philomeen is ready to die for her cause. She has run from the duergar with explosives and when the player arrives, she assumes they are a true soul and would sooner blow herself up than let the player take her to Moonrise.

If you reach the end of her dialogue, she'll leave once you get far enough away.
